<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-04T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-04T06:00:00-05:00" n="14" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/531:
                        Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-04T12:00:00+01:00">May 4,
                            1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 4—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>35. Mr. Sandler informed me yesterday that he had instructed the Swedish
                        Minister at Bern to keep Mr. Wilson fully informed with respect to the
                        subject of the Department’s telegram No. 8, April 27, 6 p.m. Have advised
                        Wilson.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>